caption: So working as a delivery driver for Postmates I just had the worst experience with any type of customer service experience I've ever had not only did they give my customers food out they seem to be not concerned at all the the bartender working in the late evening was a white female with blonde highlights in her hair and she was rude from the jump when I told reminded her I was out waiting on a Postmates order she said it will be ready when it's ready although I was only trying to ask for water while I waited the service all around was just terrible and now I have an unsatisfied customer after waiting 30 minutes just to find out they gave my customers order out I will be contacting management and I will update this review to let everybody know how management handled this situation

I would give zero 🌟,  charging more to some customers than others. Not cool !!!

Brad - the manager, kicks us out of our seats after two hours! We came in, asked if we could use the outdoor seating for the entire concert, both hostess stations said if it was open we could.  So after two hours and $250+ in liquor bills, our party of four and 7 other people on the patio get 'removed' due to a new party that booked...... after the concert starts. I pay $200 to 'reserve' my table, to find out the people next to me got it for free since they "knew someone". I complain, and get a $75 tab for my 'troubles and am told after paying $200 I don't HAVE to sit there. And I can just leave.  Would NEVER go back.

This bar deserves two ratings: One for the bar/game scene, and the other rating for the restaurant/food portion.  Bar/Game Portion: This place does it entirely right. They have a lot of activities if you're just looking to drink and hang out, and don't have a backyard in Louisville (i.e. - visitors like myself) to hang out in. Drinks are relatively cheap, but I get the impression they're probably pricey for Louisville as a whole.  Food: This is where they deserve a 1 star if not 0 stars. You're better off eating at McDonald's as the quality there is better.  Average = 2.5 Stars, which rounds up to a 3. I hope they see this and improve the menu options. I'm in the area a lot on business!

Very large open bar with patios that overlook the rest of the 4th St live district. It has a very unique design with drinks served in mason jars and they have every kind of bar game you can imagine from corn hole, to pool to bocce ball, arcade games. Really fun environment sad we did not find it until our last night in town.

I liked it here OK. They had good IPAs on draft and the bartender was decently friendly. Some of the games didnt work and one took our money but the staff refunded us. We wanted to get some food around midnight on a recent Saturday and so we sat down in a booth. We waited for maybe 15 minutes and no one came over at all. We went next door to TGI Fridays.

IT WAS ABSOLUTELY DISGUSTING. My whole entire family now has stomach aches due to their horribly burnt food. Do NOT eat here. NOT GOOD! The tator tots were harder than rocks. I think I chipped a tooth on one... Plain simple, don't eat here

Awesome bar! From our of town and had no clue what fun we were about to walk into.  You can play cornhole, bocce ball and all other lawn games, plus a few of the best arcade games and skeeball and bubble hockey.  The atmosphere is great and entertainment tops. Don't miss Battleship!
